The paper also discusses the applicability of connectionism to sociotechnical system modeling and design, which suggests that it may belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the organization of connectionist networks, which suggests that it may belong to the Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the practical application of connectionism, which suggests that it may belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
